      • add

        public boolean add​(T owner,
                   E associate)
            throws Exception
        Adds an associate to the collection of associates.

        This implementation calls getAssociates(Object) to get the collection of associates. If null it creates a new collection and sets it on the owner (using newAssociates() and setAssociates(Object, Collection)). The associate is added using Collection.add(Object).

        Parameters:
        owner - association owner
        associate - the associate to add to the collection
        Returns:
        same as Collection.add(Object)
        Throws:
        Exception

      • setAssociates

        protected void setAssociates​(T owner,
                             Collection<E> associates)
                      throws Exception
        Sets the collection of associates.

        This method is called when a manager method is called to modify the collection and getAssociates(Object) returns null. The default implementation throws UnsupportedOperationException.

        If your implementation of getAssociates(Object) can return null, you must override this method to allow the collection to be initialized.

        Parameters:
        owner - the association owner
        Throws:
        Exception

      • newAssociates

        protected Collection<E> newAssociates()
        Creates a new (empty) associates collection.

        The default implementation returns a LinkedHashSet. Override if you wish to use a different Collection subtype.

        Returns:
        collection of associates (never null)
